(42, 11, 39, 42, 16, 15, 15, 'your inward part is full of ravening', 'Connection of Inner and Outer Purity', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between outward appearances and inner morality. The focus on what is esteemed by men versus what God knows highlights the theme of true righteousness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 39, 43, 12, 6, 6, 'full of ravening and wickedness', 'Hypocrisy and Inner Corruption', 'This connection highlights the theme of outward appearances versus inner reality. Both passages emphasize the contrast between external cleanliness and internal wickedness, as seen in the Pharisees'' actions and Judas''s character.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 40, 42, 12, 20, 20, 'Ye fools', 'Foolishness and Accountability', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of foolishness in relation to one''s priorities. In Luke 11:40, the focus is on the foolishness of neglecting inner spiritual matters, while Luke 12:20 highlights the folly of hoarding material wealth without regard for one''s soul.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 40, 46, 15, 36, 36, 'Ye fools', 'Connection of Foolishness and Growth', 'This connection highlights the theme of foolishness in both passages. Each verse addresses the concept of understanding deeper truths about creation and transformation, emphasizing that true insight involves recognizing the relationship between the physical and spiritual realms.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 40, 20, 8, 5, 5, 'ye fools', 'Wisdom and Foolishness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of foolishness and the need for understanding. Luke addresses fools regarding their lack of insight, while Proverbs calls for the simple to gain wisdom and understanding.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 40, 40, 23, 17, 17, 'Ye fools', 'Connection of Foolishness and Value', 'Both passages emphasize the folly of valuing external appearances over intrinsic worth. They question the understanding of what is truly significant, whether it be the gold or the temple, or the external versus the internal.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 40, 40, 23, 26, 26, 'that which is within', 'Inner vs. Outer Cleanliness', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of inner purity over external appearances. They highlight the idea that true cleanliness begins within, suggesting that the Creator made both the inner and outer aspects of a person.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 40, 1, 1, 26, 26, 'that which is without make that which is within', 'Creation and Inner Nature', 'This connection highlights the relationship between the Creator and His creation. Both passages emphasize that God made humanity in His image, suggesting a link between the external and internal aspects of human beings.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 40, 1, 2, 7, 7, 'that which is without make that which is within', 'Creation of Inner and Outer Being', 'This connection highlights the relationship between the physical and spiritual aspects of humanity. Luke 11:40 emphasizes the creator of both the external and internal, while Genesis 2:7 describes God''s formation of man from dust and the impartation of life.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 41, 42, 12, 33, 33, 'give alms', 'Connection of Almsgiving Teachings', 'Both passages emphasize the act of giving alms as a means of spiritual investment. They highlight the importance of using earthly possessions to create lasting treasures in heaven.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 41, 56, 1, 15, 15, 'all things are clean unto you', 'Purity and Cleanliness Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of purity, stating that ''all things are clean'' for those who are pure. This connection highlights the idea that one''s internal state influences their perception of purity and cleanliness.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 41, 59, 1, 27, 27, 'give alms of such things as ye have', 'Connection of Almsgiving and Care', 'This connection highlights the importance of caring for others, as both passages emphasize acts of charity and compassion. Luke 11:41 encourages giving alms, while James 1:27 defines pure religion as visiting those in need.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 41, 44, 10, 15, 15, 'all things are clean unto you', 'Cleansing and Almsgiving Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of what is considered clean or acceptable. Both passages emphasize that what God has cleansed should not be deemed common, paralleling the idea of giving alms as a means of purity.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 41, 58, 13, 16, 16, 'give alms of such things as ye have', 'Connection of Almsgiving and Good Deeds', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of doing good and giving to others. Luke highlights giving alms as a clean act, while Hebrews encourages not forgetting to do good and communicate, which pleases God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 41, 20, 14, 31, 31, 'alms of such things as ye have', 'Connection of Almsgiving and Mercy', 'This connection highlights the importance of caring for the poor. Both passages emphasize the value of mercy and generosity towards those in need.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 41, 20, 19, 17, 17, 'give alms of such things as ye have', 'Connection of Almsgiving and Pity', 'This connection highlights the importance of giving to the poor. Both passages emphasize that acts of charity are valued and rewarded, linking the act of giving alms to divine approval and repayment.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 42, 40, 23, 23, 23, 'these ought ye to have done', 'Woes to the Pharisees', 'Both passages emphasize the Pharisees'' focus on tithing while neglecting more important matters like judgment and love. This connection highlights a critique of their priorities in religious practice.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 42, 20, 21, 3, 3, 'judgment and the love of God', 'Justice Over Rituals', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of justice and judgment over mere ritualistic practices. Luke 11:42 criticizes the Pharisees for neglecting the love of God while focusing on tithing, paralleling Proverbs 21:3, which states that doing justice is more acceptable than sacrifice.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 42, 42, 18, 12, 12, 'tithe', 'Connection of Tithing Practices', 'Both passages emphasize the practice of tithing, highlighting the Pharisees'' meticulousness in giving while neglecting deeper spiritual matters. The mention of tithing in both contexts illustrates a focus on external religious observance over internal virtues.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 42, 5, 10, 12, 13, 'the love of God', 'Connection of Love and Obedience', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of love and obedience to God. Luke highlights the need for love of God alongside proper practices, while Deuteronomy outlines the requirement to love and serve God fully.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 42, 33, 6, 8, 8, 'the love of God', 'Emphasis on Justice and Love', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of justice and love, with Luke highlighting the neglect of judgment and the love of God, while Micah calls for doing justly and loving mercy. This connection highlights the need for inner righteousness over mere ritual observance.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 42, 39, 3, 8, 8, 'tithe', 'Connection of Tithing and Judgment', 'This connection highlights the theme of tithing and its relationship to God''s expectations. Both passages emphasize the importance of tithes while also addressing the neglect of justice and love.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 42, 62, 4, 20, 20, 'the love of God', 'Love and Judgment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of love and judgment. Luke 11:42 critiques the Pharisees for neglecting love while focusing on minor rituals, while 1 John 4:20 asserts that true love for God is demonstrated through love for others.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 43, 42, 20, 46, 46, NULL, 'Critique of Religious Leaders', 'Both passages emphasize the love of greetings in the markets and the desire for prominent seating in synagogues, highlighting the hypocrisy of religious leaders. This connection illustrates a consistent critique of the behavior of the Pharisees and scribes.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 43, 41, 12, 38, 39, 'uppermost seats in the synagogues', 'Pharisees and Scribes'' Behavior', 'Both passages emphasize the love of prominent positions and public recognition by religious leaders. The phrases about ''uppermost seats'' and ''salutations in the marketplaces'' highlight a shared critique of their behavior.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 43, 40, 23, 6, 7, 'love the uppermost seats in the synagogues', 'Connection of Pharisaic Pride', 'Both passages emphasize the Pharisees'' love for prominent positions and public recognition. They highlight the same behaviors regarding social status and titles.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 43, 42, 14, 7, 11, 'the uppermost seats', 'Connection of Humility and Exaltation', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of humility over seeking honor. The warning against loving ''the uppermost seats'' in Luke 11:43 parallels the teaching in Luke 14:7-11 about choosing the lowest room to avoid shame.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 43, 20, 16, 18, 18, NULL, 'Connection of Pride and Consequences', 'Both passages emphasize the dangers of pride and haughtiness. Luke 11:43 warns against the love of status, while Proverbs 16:18 states that pride leads to destruction.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 43, 45, 12, 10, 10, NULL, 'Contrast in Attitudes Toward Honor', 'This connection highlights the contrasting attitudes toward honor and recognition. While Luke 11:43 criticizes the Pharisees for seeking honor, Romans 12:10 encourages believers to prefer one another in honor.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
